maps.name: Afternoon hike at Wachusett Mountain Old Indian, Stage Coach, Bicentennial Trails
Via Alpina Green Trail: Griesalp - Kandersteg (Hoturli and Oeschinensee)
maps.comment:
Amazing scenery helped with the grind of a climb as the switchbacks slowly narrowed. I lost count of the steps up to Hotürli pass, the highest point on the Via Alpina.

The hut at the pass is another 7 minute hike further uphill. It was ice cream day so we had to have some. Nice views of the glacier, and a cool cliff to climb if you're brave.

The lake was scenic, blue, and cold, but not too cold for a dip!

maps.name: Via Alpina: Murren - Griesalp
maps.description:
Perfect weather and ridiculously beautiful. Stopped for a beer (supplied by helicopter) at the rotstockhutte before ascending to the pass. Then descended through paradise itself for several hours to reach Hotel Golderli and prepare for the next stage.

Trail is in great condition. Well signed and not too slippery on this segment.

Glad we skipped the first few thousand feet of gain by taking the gondola!
